@startuml OmniEdgeAI_Architecture

title OmniEdge_AI — Microservice Architecture & Browser Interaction\nEdge AI Assistant · WSL2 · 4–16+ GB VRAM (4 tiers) · 9 Independent C++ Processes
autonumber

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam maxmessagesize 220
skinparam sequenceParticipant underline
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #616161
skinparam sequenceGroupHeaderFontSize 13

' ── Participants ──────────────────────────────────────────
' Each box = independent OS process (microservice).
' Communication: ZMQ (control) + POSIX shm (data) only.
' No process links to another's library or calls its functions.
' SHM segments shown as self-arrows on producer/consumer.

box "Ingestion" #E8F5E9
    participant "Video Ingest\nGStreamer · Port 5555" as GSV
    participant "Audio Ingest\nGStreamer · Port 5556" as GSA
end box

box "ZMQ PUB/SUB Bus" #FFF3E0
    participant "ZeroMQ\nTCP localhost" as ZMQ
end box

box "Vision Nodes" #FCE4EC
    participant "InspireFace\nFP16 ~0.5 GB\nPort 5566" as FR
    participant "Background Blur\nYOLOv8-seg FP16 ~0.5 GB\nPort 5567" as BB
    participant "Moondream2\nINT4 2.45 GB\nPort 5562" as VLM
end box

box "Audio / Language Nodes" #FCE4EC
    participant "Whisper V3\nINT8 1.5 GB\nPort 5563" as STT
    participant "Qwen 2.5 7B\nINT4 4.3 GB\nPort 5561" as LLM
    participant "Kokoro v1.0\nINT8 0.1 GB\nPort 5565" as TTS
    participant "FLUX.1-schnell\nINT8 4.5 GB (on-demand)\nPort 5568" as IMGGEN
end box

box "Frontend" #F3E5F5
    participant "uWebSockets\nC++ :9001 · ZMQ Port 5570\n/video /audio /chat" as UWS
    participant "Browser JS\nCanvas+AudioCtx" as UI
end box

box "Daemon" #EFEBE9
    participant "OmniEdgeDaemon\nWatchdog · ZMQ Port 5571" as DAEMON
end box


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 1 — SYSTEM BOOT
' ==============================================================

== Phase 1: System Boot ==

note over DAEMON
  oe_daemon is the **only** binary the user starts.
  It spawns every microservice via posix_spawn().
  Each child = independent ELF binary with own main().
  IPC boundary: ZMQ sockets + POSIX shm only.
end note

DAEMON -> GSV : posix_spawn("oe_video_ingest")\nZMQ_PUB_PORT=5555
DAEMON -> GSA : posix_spawn("oe_audio_ingest")\nZMQ_PUB_PORT=5556
DAEMON -> FR : posix_spawn("oe_face_recog")\nZMQ_PUB_PORT=5566
DAEMON -> BB : posix_spawn("oe_bg_blur")\nZMQ_PUB_PORT=5567
DAEMON -> STT : posix_spawn("oe_stt")\nZMQ_PUB_PORT=5563
DAEMON -> TTS : posix_spawn("oe_tts")\nZMQ_PUB_PORT=5565
DAEMON -> VLM : posix_spawn("oe_vlm")\nZMQ_PUB_PORT=5562
DAEMON -> LLM : posix_spawn("oe_llm")\nZMQ_PUB_PORT=5561
DAEMON -> UWS : posix_spawn("oe_ws_bridge")\nHTTP_PORT=9001

note over DAEMON
  All children report HEALTHY on heartbeat
  sockets before daemon enters watchdog loop.
  Boot target: < 8 seconds.
  Daemon loads omniedge_config.yaml at startup
  and maintains a conversation state machine (7 states):
  IDLE → LISTENING → PROCESSING → SPEAKING
  PROCESSING_VISION (VLM on-demand)
  INTERRUPTED (barge-in) → LISTENING
  ERROR_RECOVERY (module crash → restart)
  (see Conversation Orchestration section).
end note


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 2 — BROWSER CONNECTS (JS initiates everything)
' ==============================================================

== Phase 2: Browser Opens — 3 WebSocket Channels ==

UI -> UI : window.onload fires

note over UI
  **JS connection setup:**
  const wsVideo = new WebSocket("ws://localhost:9001/video");
  const wsAudio = new WebSocket("ws://localhost:9001/audio");
  const wsChat  = new WebSocket("ws://localhost:9001/chat");
  wsVideo.binaryType = "arraybuffer";
  wsAudio.binaryType = "arraybuffer";
end note

UI -> UWS : WebSocket("ws://localhost:9001/video")
UWS -> UWS : ws<VideoCtx>("/video",\n{.open=[](ws){clients_video.push_back(ws);}})

UI -> UWS : WebSocket("ws://localhost:9001/audio")
UWS -> UWS : ws<AudioCtx>("/audio",\n{.open=[](ws){clients_audio.push_back(ws);}})

UI -> UWS : WebSocket("ws://localhost:9001/chat")
UWS -> UWS : ws<ChatCtx>("/chat",\n{.open=[](ws){clients_chat.push_back(ws);}})

note over UWS
  **C++ bridge threading model:**
  Thread 1: uWS event loop (WebSocket I/O)
  Thread 2: zmq_poll() on all SUB sockets
  Data passed via thread-safe queue +
  uWS::Loop::defer() to avoid lock contention.
end note


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 3 — VIDEO PIPELINE
' ==============================================================

== Phase 3: Video — Webcam -> GPU -> JPEG -> Canvas ==

note over GSV
  **Input:** Webcam H.264 over TCP :5000
  from Windows host (ksvideosrc x264enc
  tune=zerolatency bitrate=16000000)
end note

group Video Ingest [oe_video_ingest]
    GSV -> GSV : GStreamer pipeline:\ntcpclientsrc → H.264 decode\n→ BGR24 conversion → appsink
    GSV -> GSV : appsink callback fires:\nextract GstBuffer, map memory
    GSV -> GSV : Write 6.2 MB BGR frame to\n/oe.vid.ingest (double-buffer slot)\nincrement sequence_number + timestamp
    GSV -> ZMQ : PUB "video_frame"\n{shm:"/oe.vid.ingest", seq:N}
end

note over ZMQ
  **ZMQ_CONFLATE=1** on data-plane topics only:
  video_frame, audio_chunk, blurred_frame, identity.
  Control topics (llm_prompt, transcription, etc.)
  use ZMQ_CONFLATE=0 (queue all, in-order).
end note

group Face Recognition [oe_face_recog — InspireFace]
    ZMQ -> FR : SUB "video_frame"\ntcp://localhost:5555
    FR -> FR : **shm read /oe.vid.ingest**\nmemcpy(pinned_buf, shm_ptr, frame_size)
    note right of FR
      cudaHostRegister unsupported on WSL2.
      Must use cudaHostAlloc staging buffer.
    end note
    FR -> FR : cudaMemcpyAsync(d_input,\npinned_buf, size, H2D, stream)
    FR -> FR : HF_FaceDetect -> vector<FaceRect>\nHF_FaceAlign -> aligned_chip\nHF_FaceFeatureExtract -> float[512]\nHF_FaceComparison(emb, gallery)\n-> {name, confidence}
    FR -> ZMQ : PUB "identity"\n{name:"Admin", conf:0.98}
end

group Background Blur [oe_bg_blur — YOLOv8-seg + adjust + shapes]
    ZMQ -> BB : SUB "video_frame"\ntcp://localhost:5555
    ZMQ -> BB : SUB "ui_command"\ntcp://localhost:5570\n(set_image_adjust, update_shapes)
    BB -> BB : **shm read /oe.vid.ingest**\ncudaMemcpyAsync via pinned buf
    BB -> BB : enqueueV2({d_input, d_mask})\n// YOLOv8-seg [1,3,640,640] FP16
    BB -> BB : cudaStreamSynchronize(stream)\ncv::cuda::resize(mask, {1920,1080})
    BB -> BB : cv::cuda::GaussianBlur(frame,\nblurred, {51,51}, 25.0, stream)
    BB -> BB : Composite: out[i] =\nmask[i] ? sharp[i] : blurred[i]
    BB -> BB : applyImageAdjustments(bright,\ncontrast, sat, sharp) // CUDA
    BB -> BB : renderShapes(shapes, mask)\n// CPU draw + mask-aware composite
    BB -> BB : nvjpegEncode(output, quality=85)\n-> jpeg_buf, jpeg_size
    BB -> BB : **shm write /oe.cv.blur.jpeg**\nmemcpy(shm_ptr, jpeg_buf, jpeg_size)
    BB -> ZMQ : PUB "blurred_frame"\n{shm:"/oe.cv.blur.jpeg", size:N}
end

group VLM Scene Description [oe_vlm — Moondream2]
    ZMQ -> VLM : SUB "video_frame"\ntcp://localhost:5555
    note right of VLM
      Periodic (every 5 s) or on-demand
      via "describe_scene" UI command.
      Drops frames via ZMQ_CONFLATE.
    end note
    VLM -> VLM : **shm read /oe.vid.ingest**\ncv::resize(frame, {378,378})\nnormalize, cudaMemcpyAsync
    VLM -> VLM : SigLIP encoder:\nimage_features = encoder->enqueueV2()\n// [1, 729, 2048] feature tensor
    VLM -> VLM : Text decoder loop:\nfor (i=0; i<max_tokens; i++) {\n  logits = decoder->enqueueV2(\n    {image_features, token_ids})\n  tok = argmax(logits)\n  if (tok==EOS) break;\n}
    VLM -> VLM : detokenize(token_ids) -> description
    VLM -> ZMQ : PUB "vlm_description"\n{text:"A person at a desk..."}
end

note over UWS
  **Bridge receives blurred_frame:**
  zmq_poll -> read JPEG from shm
  -> uWS::Loop::defer([&]{
    for (ws : clients_video)
      ws->send({jpeg, size}, BINARY);
  })
end note

ZMQ -> UWS : SUB "blurred_frame" (port 5567)
UWS -> UWS : shm read /oe.cv.blur.jpeg
UWS -> UI : ws.send(jpeg_bytes, {binary:true})\n// /video ~30 fps

note over UI
  **JS video rendering:**
  wsVideo.onmessage = (event) => {
    const blob = new Blob(
      [event.data], {type:"image/jpeg"});
    const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
    const img = new Image();
    img.onload = () => {
      ctx.drawImage(img, 0, 0,
        canvas.width, canvas.height);
      URL.revokeObjectURL(url);
    };
    img.src = url;
  };
end note


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 4 — AUDIO PIPELINE
' ==============================================================

== Phase 4: Audio — Mic -> STT -> LLM -> TTS -> Speaker ==

note over GSA
  **Input:** Microphone PCM F32 over TCP :5001
  from Windows host (wasapi2src 16 kHz mono)
end note

group Audio Ingest [oe_audio_ingest + Silero VAD]
    GSA -> GSA : GstPipeline: tcpclientsrc\n-> audioconvert -> audioresample\n-> appsink (F32LE, rate=16000)
    GSA -> GSA : **Silero VAD filter (CPU, <1ms):**\nspeech_prob = vad_session.Run(chunk)\nif (speech_prob < 0.5) discard;
    note right of GSA
      VAD gates every audio chunk.
      Prevents Whisper hallucinations on
      silence/noise. Only speech reaches shm.
      Silero VAD: ~1 MB ONNX, CPU only, 0 VRAM.
    end note
    GSA -> GSA : **shm write /oe.aud.ingest**\nmemcpy(shm_ptr, pcm_f32, samples*4)
    GSA -> ZMQ : PUB "audio_chunk"\n{shm:"/oe.aud.ingest", vad:"speech"}
    GSA -> ZMQ : (on 1.5s silence after speech)\nPUB "vad_status"\n{speaking:false, silence_ms:1500}
end

group STT [oe_stt — Whisper V3 Turbo]
    ZMQ -> STT : SUB "audio_chunk"\ntcp://localhost:5556
    STT -> STT : **shm read /oe.aud.ingest**\nring_buffer.append(pcm_chunk)\n// 30 s sliding window, 1 s overlap
    STT -> STT : 128-bin Log-Mel spectrogram:\nfor each 25ms window (10ms hop):\n  fft = rfft(window * hann)\n  mel = filterbank @ |fft|^2\n  log_mel = log(max(mel, 1e-10))
    STT -> STT : cudaMemcpyAsync(d_mel, log_mel)\nencoder->enqueueV2({d_mel, d_hidden})\n// mel -> encoder hidden states
    STT -> STT : Decoder loop:\nwhile (!eos && n < 448) {\n  logits = decoder->enqueueV2(\n    {d_hidden, d_token_ids})\n  tok = argmax(logits[-1])\n  tokens.push_back(tok)\n}
    STT -> STT : text = tokenizer.decode(tokens)\nlang = detect_language(logits[0])
    STT -> ZMQ : PUB "transcription"\n{text:"Hello OmniEdge", lang:"en"}
end


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 5 — LLM REASONING
' ==============================================================

== Phase 5: Daemon Orchestration — Fuses All Inputs → LLM ==

note over DAEMON
  **OmniEdgeDaemon subscribes to ALL sensor outputs.**
  It caches latest identity + scene description.
  On new transcription → assembles full prompt
  → publishes "llm_prompt" on port 5571.
  QwenLLM subscribes ONLY to daemon (port 5571).
end note

group Daemon Prompt Assembly [oe_daemon — State Machine]
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : SUB "transcription" (port 5563)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : SUB "identity" (port 5566)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : SUB "vlm_description" (port 5562)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : SUB "vad_status" (port 5556)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : SUB "ui_command" (port 5570)\n(push_to_talk, text_input,\ndescribe_scene, cancel_generation)

    DAEMON -> DAEMON : State: LISTENING → PROCESSING\nassemble prompt from cached context:\nsystem (200 tok) + face identity (20 tok)\n+ scene (80 tok) + history (2796 tok)\n+ user utterance (500 tok)
    DAEMON -> ZMQ : PUB "llm_prompt" (port 5571)\n{v:1, system:"...", user:"...",\nidentity:"Admin", scene:"...",\nhistory:[...]}
end

group LLM [oe_llm — Qwen 2.5 7B]
    ZMQ -> LLM : SUB "llm_prompt" (port 5571)\n// ONLY subscribes to daemon

    note over LLM
      **LLM receives fully assembled prompt**
      from daemon (port 5571). It does NOT
      subscribe to raw sensor topics.
      KV cache: 1.15 GB (FP8 on Blackwell SM10.0+)
      Max context: 4096 tokens (standard tier)
    end note

    LLM -> LLM : prompt = parseLlmPrompt(msg)\ntoken_ids = encode(prompt)\nassert(len <= max_seq_len)
    LLM -> LLM : **TRT-LLM GptSession:**\nsession.setup(batch=1, max_new=512)\nwhile (!finished) {\n  session.step(d_logits)\n  tok = top_p_sample(\n    d_logits, temp=0.7, p=0.9)\n  if (tok==eos) finished=true;
    LLM -> ZMQ : PUB "llm_response" (streamed)\n{token:"Hello", finished:false}\n// ~40 tok/s on RTX PRO 3000 (12 GB)
    LLM -> ZMQ : PUB "llm_response"\n{token:"", finished:true}
end


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 6 — TTS
' ==============================================================

== Phase 6: TTS — LLM Tokens -> Audio -> Browser ==

group TTS [oe_tts — Kokoro v1.0]
    ZMQ -> TTS : SUB "llm_response" (port 5561)
    TTS -> TTS : **Sentence accumulation:**\nbuf += tok; if (buf.ends_with('.')\n|| buf.ends_with('?') || finished)\n  sentence = buf; buf.clear();
    TTS -> TTS : **espeak-ng G2P:**\nipa = espeak_text_to_phonemes(\n  sentence, "en", IPA)\nids = phoneme_to_id_map(ipa)
    TTS -> TTS : **ONNX Runtime inference:**\ninput_ids = CreateTensor(ids)\nstyle = load_npy("af_heart.npy")\noutput = session.Run({ids, style})\npcm = output[0].GetTensorData<float>()
    TTS -> TTS : **shm write /oe.aud.tts**\nmemcpy(shm, pcm, samples*4)\nheader->sample_rate = 24000
    TTS -> ZMQ : PUB "tts_audio"\n{shm:"/oe.aud.tts", rate:24000}
end

note over UWS
  **Bridge receives tts_audio:**
  zmq_poll -> shm read /oe.aud.tts
  -> convert float32 -> int16
  -> defer send to /audio clients
end note

ZMQ -> UWS : SUB "tts_audio" (port 5565)
UWS -> UWS : shm read /oe.aud.tts\nfloat32 -> int16 conversion
UWS -> UI : ws.send(pcm_int16, {binary:true})\n// /audio channel

note over UI
  **JS audio playback:**
  const audioCtx = new AudioContext(
    {sampleRate: 24000});
  let audioQueue = [], isPlaying = false;

  wsAudio.onmessage = (event) => {
    const pcm16 = new Int16Array(event.data);
    const f32 = new Float32Array(pcm16.length);
    for (let i=0; i<pcm16.length; i++)
      f32[i] = pcm16[i] / 32768.0;
    const buf = audioCtx.createBuffer(
      1, f32.length, 24000);
    buf.getChannelData(0).set(f32);
    audioQueue.push(buf);
    if (!isPlaying) playNext();
  };

  function playNext() {
    if (!audioQueue.length)
      { isPlaying=false; return; }
    isPlaying = true;
    const src = audioCtx.createBufferSource();
    src.buffer = audioQueue.shift();
    src.connect(audioCtx.destination);
    src.onended = playNext;
    src.start();
  }
end note


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 7 — CHAT TOKEN STREAMING
' ==============================================================

== Phase 7: Chat — Streamed Tokens -> Browser ==

ZMQ -> UWS : SUB "llm_response" (port 5561)
UWS -> UI : ws.send(JSON.stringify(msg))\n// /chat text frame

note over UI
  **JS chat rendering:**
  let bubble = null;
  wsChat.onmessage = (event) => {
    const msg = JSON.parse(event.data);
    if (!bubble) {
      bubble = document.createElement("div");
      bubble.className = "chat-bubble assistant";
      chatContainer.appendChild(bubble);
    }
    bubble.textContent += msg.token;
    chatContainer.scrollTop =
      chatContainer.scrollHeight;
    if (msg.finished) bubble = null;
  };
end note


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 8 — USER-INITIATED ACTIONS (JS -> Backend)
' ==============================================================

== Phase 8: User Actions — JS Triggers Backend ==

note over UI
  **All UI interactions follow one pattern:**
  JS click -> WebSocket JSON -> uWS parse
  -> ZMQ PUB "ui_command" -> microservice
end note

' ── Action A: Push-to-Talk ──
group Push-to-Talk (PTT) #FFEBEE
    UI -> UI : btn-ptt mousedown:\nwsChat.send(JSON.stringify(\n  {action:"push_to_talk",state:true}));
    UI -> UWS : /chat text frame\n{action:"push_to_talk", state:true}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (port 5570)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : Daemon: state IDLE → LISTENING
    DAEMON -> GSA : Start audio capture\ngst_element_set_state(PLAYING)
    note over DAEMON
      **State machine transitions (7 states, 23 transitions):**
      PTT press  → IDLE → LISTENING
      PTT release → LISTENING → PROCESSING
      VAD 1.5s silence → auto PROCESSING
      DESCRIBE_SCENE → IDLE → PROCESSING_VISION
      Barge-in (PTT during SPEAKING)
      → INTERRUPTED → LISTENING
      MODULE_CRASH → ERROR_RECOVERY → IDLE
    end note
    UI -> UI : btn-ptt mouseup:\nwsChat.send({action:\n  "push_to_talk",state:false});
    UI -> UWS : {action:"push_to_talk",state:false}
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : Daemon: LISTENING → PROCESSING\nassemble prompt → send to LLM
end

' ── Action B: Disable Webcam ──
group Disable Webcam #E3F2FD
    UI -> UI : btn-webcam click:\nwsChat.send({action:\n  "disable_webcam", state:true})
    UI -> UWS : {action:"disable_webcam", state:true}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (port 5570)
    ZMQ -> GSV : gst_element_set_state(\n  pipeline, GST_STATE_PAUSED)\n// FR,BB,VLM starve. Canvas frozen.
end

' ── Action C: Text Chat (bypass STT) ──
group Text Chat Input #E8F5E9
    UI -> UI : chatInput "Enter" handler:\nconst text = chatInput.value.trim();\nappendBubble("user", text);\nwsChat.send({action:\n  "text_input", text: text});
    UI -> UWS : {action:"text_input",\ntext:"What do you see?"}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (port 5570)\n{action:"text_input",\ntext:"What do you see?"}
    note over DAEMON
      text_input bypasses STT entirely.
      Daemon receives it as a ui_command,
      assembles prompt identically to a
      PTT transcription, and publishes
      llm_prompt on port 5571.
    end note
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : SUB "ui_command"\n-> TEXT_INPUT event
    DAEMON -> DAEMON : assemblePrompt(text)\nstate: IDLE → PROCESSING
    DAEMON -> ZMQ : PUB "llm_prompt" (port 5571)\n{system:"...", user:"What do you see?",\nhistory:[...]}
    ZMQ -> LLM : SUB "llm_prompt" (port 5571)\n-> triggers Phase 5 LLM inference
    LLM -> ZMQ : PUB "llm_response" (stream)
    ZMQ -> UWS : -> Phase 7 chat rendering
    ZMQ -> TTS : -> Phase 6 TTS synthesis
end

' ── Action D: Register Face ──
group Register Face #F3E5F5
    UI -> UI : btn-register-face click:\nOpen file picker OR capture webcam snapshot
    UI -> UWS : /chat binary frame\n{action:"register_face",\nname:"Admin", image: <JPEG bytes>}
    UWS -> UWS : Decode JPEG → BGR buffer\nWrite to temp shm /oe.vid.register
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (port 5570)\n{action:"register_face",\nname:"Admin", shm:"/oe.vid.register"}
    ZMQ -> FR : SUB "ui_command"\nRead BGR from /oe.vid.register
    FR -> FR : HF_FaceDetect → crop face\nHF_FaceAlign → aligned chip\nHF_FaceFeatureExtract → float[512]
    FR -> FR : INSERT INTO known_faces\n(name, embedding) VALUES (...)
    FR -> ZMQ : PUB "face_registered"\n{name:"Admin", success:true}
    ZMQ -> UWS : SUB "face_registered" (port 5566)
    UWS -> UI : /chat JSON\n{type:"face_registered",\nname:"Admin", success:true}
    note over UI
      showToast("Face registered: Admin");
      // Future frames will identify
      // this person by name.
    end note
end

' ── Action E: Describe Scene ──
group Describe Scene #FFF3E0
    UI -> UI : btn-describe click:\nwsChat.send(\n  {action:"describe_scene"})
    UI -> UWS : {action:"describe_scene"}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (port 5570)
    ZMQ -> VLM : SUB "ui_command"\nforce_inference_now = true\n// Run Moondream2 immediately
    VLM -> ZMQ : PUB "vlm_description"\n{text:"Person at desk,\ntwo monitors, coffee mug."}
    ZMQ -> UWS : SUB "vlm_description" (5562)
    UWS -> UI : /chat JSON\n{type:"vlm", text:description}
    note over UI
      if (msg.type === "vlm")
        appendBubble("system",
          "Scene: " + msg.text);
    end note
end

' ── Action F: Image Adjustments ──
group Image Adjustments #E0F7FA
    UI -> UI : Slider change (debounced 10/s):\nwsChat.send({action:\n  "set_image_adjust", adjust:{\n  brightness:0.2, contrast:1.1,\n  saturation:1.3, sharpness:1.5}})
    UI -> UWS : {action:"set_image_adjust",\nadjust:{brightness:0.2,...}}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (port 5570)
    ZMQ -> BB : SUB "ui_command"\ncache ImageAdjust struct atomically\n// Applied per-frame in GPU pipeline
    note over BB
      If all values are defaults
      (0.0, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0), the
      adjustment pipeline is skipped
      entirely — zero overhead.
    end note
end

' ── Action G: Shape Overlays ──
group Shape Overlays #E0F2F1
    UI -> UI : Canvas pointerup:\nshapeList.push(newShape);\nwsChat.send({action:\n  "update_shapes",\n  shapes: shapeList})
    UI -> UWS : {action:"update_shapes",\nshapes:[{type:"rect",...},...]}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (port 5570)
    ZMQ -> BB : SUB "ui_command"\nstore shape list, render onto\nblurred background region only\n// Foreground mask pixels untouched
end

' ── Action H: Barge-In (PTT during SPEAKING) ──
group Barge-In Interruption #FFCDD2
    note over DAEMON
      User presses PTT while assistant
      is speaking. Daemon interrupts all
      active generation within 100 ms.
    end note
    UI -> UWS : {action:"push_to_talk",\nstate:true}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (port 5570)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : state: SPEAKING → INTERRUPTED
    DAEMON -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command"\n{action:"cancel_generation"}\n→ LLM stops emitting tokens
    DAEMON -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command"\n{action:"flush_tts"}\n→ TTS clears pending sentences
    DAEMON -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command"\n{action:"stop_playback"}\n→ Frontend stops audio playback
    ZMQ -> LLM : cancel_generation received\nstop token loop immediately
    ZMQ -> TTS : flush_tts received\nclear sentence queue
    ZMQ -> UWS : stop_playback received
    UWS -> UI : {type:"stop_playback"}\naudioQueue = []; isPlaying = false;
    DAEMON -> DAEMON : state: INTERRUPTED → LISTENING\nstart audio capture pipeline
end


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 9 — WATCHDOG & HEARTBEAT
' ==============================================================

== Phase 9: Watchdog — Heartbeat & Auto-Recovery ==

note over DAEMON
  **ZMTP protocol-level PING/PONG:**
  Runs inside ZMQ I/O thread — works even
  if module's main thread is in a CUDA kernel.
  ZMQ_HEARTBEAT_IVL    = 1000 ms
  ZMQ_HEARTBEAT_TIMEOUT = 5000 ms
  ZMQ_HEARTBEAT_TTL     = 10000 ms
end note

loop Every 1000 ms (ZMTP automatic — all 9 modules)
    DAEMON --> FR : PING
    FR --> DAEMON : PONG
    DAEMON --> LLM : PING
    LLM --> DAEMON : PONG
    note over DAEMON
      Same PING/PONG for: GSV, GSA, BB,
      VLM, STT, TTS, UWS (omitted for brevity)
    end note
end

' ── Failure Recovery ──
== Failure: Face Recognition Crashes ==

FR ->x FR : SIGSEGV (corrupted TRT engine)
DAEMON --> FR : PING (no PONG within 5000 ms)
note over DAEMON : ZMQ_EVENT_DISCONNECTED fires

DAEMON -> DAEMON : kill(fr_pid, SIGTERM)\nwaitpid(fr_pid, 2s timeout)\nif (!exited) kill(SIGKILL)\nrestartCount[FR]++\nif (count > 5) {\n  logCritical("FR max restarts");\n  return; // prevent restart loop\n}
DAEMON -> FR : posix_spawn("oe_face_recog")\n// Fresh VRAM allocation

DAEMON -> UWS : PUB "module_status"\n{module:"face_recognition",status:"down"}
UWS -> UI : /chat JSON\n{type:"module_status",...}
note over UI
  **Graceful degradation (per module):**
  FR down → LLM: "User: Unknown"
  Blur down → raw video passthrough
  STT down → disable PTT, show text input
  TTS down → text-only responses
  Daemon pushes status via WebSocket.
  UI adapts in real-time.
end note


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 10 — DYNAMIC VRAM MANAGEMENT
' ==============================================================

== Phase 10: Dynamic VRAM — On-Demand Spawn & Eviction ==

note over DAEMON
  **Process-level VRAM isolation:**
  Each module = separate process with own CUDA context.
  Process exit → CUDA driver destroys context →
  ALL VRAM freed as contiguous blocks (zero fragmentation).

  **On-demand pattern (balanced tier):**
  VLM is not always loaded. When user requests
  "describe_scene", daemon spawns oe_vlm, waits
  for result, then SIGTERMs it to free VRAM.

  **Priority-based eviction:**
  When VRAM is insufficient for a spawn:
  1. Find lowest-priority IDLE module
  2. SIGTERM → waitpid → verify VRAM freed
  3. Spawn requested module
  Eviction order: Blur(0) → FR(1) → VLM(2) → TTS(3)
  QwenLLM (priority 5) is NEVER evicted.
end note

group On-Demand VLM Spawn [balanced tier example]
    UI -> UWS : {action:"describe_scene"}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (port 5570)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : handleOnDemandRequest("vlm")
    DAEMON -> DAEMON : probeGpu(0).freeMb >= 2450?\n├ YES → spawn\n└ NO  → evictLowestPriority()
    DAEMON -> VLM : posix_spawn("oe_vlm")
    VLM -> ZMQ : PUB "module_ready"
    DAEMON -> DAEMON : wait for "module_ready" (30 s timeout)
    ZMQ -> VLM : Forward "describe_scene" request
    VLM -> ZMQ : PUB "vlm_description"\n{text:"Person at desk..."}
    DAEMON -> VLM : kill(vlm_pid, SIGTERM)\n// VRAM freed: CUDA context destroyed\n// Zero fragmentation — clean as boot
end

group On-Demand FLUX Spawn [text_to_image mode]
    UI -> UWS : {action:"switch_mode",\nmode:"text_to_image"}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (port 5570)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : handleModeSwitch("text_to_image")
    DAEMON -> DAEMON : Evict STT, TTS, VLM, CV\nto free VRAM for FLUX (4.5 GB)
    DAEMON -> IMGGEN : posix_spawn("oe_img_gen")
    IMGGEN -> ZMQ : PUB "module_ready"
    DAEMON -> DAEMON : wait for "module_ready" (30 s timeout)
    UI -> UWS : {action:"generate_image",\ntext:"A sunset over mountains"}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (port 5570)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : assembleImagePrompt(text)
    DAEMON -> ZMQ : PUB "image_gen_prompt" (port 5571)
    ZMQ -> IMGGEN : SUB "image_gen_prompt" (port 5571)
    IMGGEN -> IMGGEN : CLIP tokenize → 4-step\ndenoising → VAE decode\n→ RGB 512×512 → PNG encode\n→ shm write /oe.nlp.imggen
    IMGGEN -> ZMQ : PUB "generated_image"\n{shm:"/oe.nlp.imggen", size:N}
    ZMQ -> UWS : SUB "generated_image" (port 5568)
    UWS -> UWS : shm read /oe.nlp.imggen
    UWS -> UI : ws.send(png_bytes, {binary:true})\n// /video channel
end

note over DAEMON
  **No in-process loadModel()/unloadModel().**
  Process isolation guarantees zero CUDA memory
  fragmentation over millions of load/unload cycles.
  See vram-management.md for full analysis.
end note


' ==============================================================
' VRAM BUDGET
' ==============================================================

note across
  **VRAM Budget — Standard Tier (12 GB)**
  Qwen 2.5 7B INT4-AWQ ... 4.30 GB  |  InspireFace FP16 ...... ~0.50 GB
  Moondream2 INT4 ........ 2.45 GB  |  YOLOv8-seg FP16 ....... ~0.50 GB
  Whisper V3 Turbo INT8 .. 1.50 GB  |  Kokoro v1.0 INT8 ...... ~0.10 GB
  Paged KV Cache FP8 ..... 1.15 GB  |  Silero VAD (CPU) ........ 0 GB
  System Buffer (WSL2) .... 1.50 GB  |  FLUX.1-schnell INT8 ... 4.50 GB
                                     |  (on-demand, mutually exclusive
                                     |   with STT+TTS+VLM+CV)

  Tiers: **minimal** (4 GB) · **balanced** (8 GB) · **standard** (12 GB) · **ultra** (16+ GB)
  Auto-selected at boot via probeGpu() + selectTier(); override with --profile <tier>

  **Dynamic VRAM:** Models not in use are UNLOADED (process SIGTERMed).
  On lower tiers, modules are spawned on-demand and torn down after use.
  Process-level CUDA context isolation guarantees zero VRAM fragmentation.

  **No Hardcoded Numbers:** All tuning parameters (timeouts, thresholds,
  JPEG quality, blur sigma, VAD threshold, max restarts) are read from
  omniedge_config.yaml. Only architectural constants (port assignments,
  model architectures, CUDA SM versions) are fixed in code.

  **Microservice Boundary:** Each process owns its own
  cudaSetDevice(0) context. A CUDA crash in one module
  cannot corrupt another's context.
end note

@enduml
